replies.body:
Yeah we took him out back and had him drawn an quartered so Cobra could start his hostile take over of patch chat 

{{sticker:slayer-jinx-wink}} 

As for Xayah and Rakan they are DOPE. I've played both of them quite a bit and they're exciting additions to bot lane. When played together they're strong but in particular the shared back is INSANE (you can do some crazy stuff with it, just saving 8s of back time is already crazy but you can also do some fun stuff like backing over a short wall and pulling your buddy with you). They're good champions individually and fit most teams/comps, but my two honorable mentions for these guys is the Kalista+Rakan combo and the Xayah+Thresh combo. The Kalista+Rakan combo is particularly fun, partially because their synergies are nutty for engage, partially because you get to make relationship jokes the entire time (you're married to ME now forget that Xayah person). Xayah Thresh is the "you will never kill this marksman" combo- lantern + Xayah R is pretty strong and the hook+flay is often enough delay for Xayah to stack 3 feathers for the root on E. Nasty combo.
